    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2008 Corvette Z06 is a purist\u2019s performance machine, powered by the hand-assembled LS7 7.0L V8. This high-revving mill features titanium connecting rods and a dry-sump lubrication system, ensuring consistent oil pressure under high lateral G-loads. The aluminum frame and magnesium engine cradle provide a lightweight, rigid foundation that distinguishes the Z06 from the base C6. The Tremec TR-6060 six-speed manual transmission delivers precise throws, and the 3.42 limited-slip rear differential provides aggressive off-the-line torque. Mechanical health is a priority; the cylinder heads have been professionally addressed to mitigate valve guide wear, and the cooling system has been flushed with fresh Dex-Cool. It sits on a staggered set of lightweight alloys wrapped in Michelin Pilot Super Sport tires. The braking system utilizes six-piston front and four-piston rear monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors for exceptional thermal management and stopping power. A mechanically sound example ready for the apex.",
